<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3284] In master when handling a split, the offline of parent and online of children is not done atomically</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3284</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In AssignmentManager.handleSplitReport() we do:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;    regionOffline(parent);
    regionOnline(a, hsi);
    regionOnline(b, hsi);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Within each of these, there is locking, but there is no locking around this entire operation.  There should be.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This might be the cause of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3278&quot; title=&quot;AssertionError in LoadBalancer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3278&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3278&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
